== Simple usage ==
# <code>{{tld|{{BASEPAGENAME}}}}</code> uses a left-aligned thumbnail image with the file name determined from the name of the article (<code>"PAGENAME" track.png</code>)
# <code>{{tld|{{BASEPAGENAME}}|''filename''}}</code> uses a left-aligned thumbnail image with the file name set to <code>''filename''</code> and caption set to "Storm path"
# <code>{{tld|{{BASEPAGENAME}}|''filename''|right}}</code> uses a right-aligned thumbnail image with the file name set to <code>''filename''</code> and caption set to "Storm path".
# <code>{{tld|{{BASEPAGENAME}}|''filename''|right|''size''}}</code> uses a right-aligned thumbnail image with the file name set to <code>''filename''</code>, and size set to <code>''size''</code> and caption set to "Storm path".
# <code>{{tld|{{BASEPAGENAME}}|''filename''|right|''size''|''caption''}}</code> uses a right-aligned thumbnail image with the file name set to <code>''filename''</code>, and size set to <code>''size''</code> and caption set to <code>''caption''</code>.

To set the value for the [[WP:ALT|alternative text]], use {{para|alt|''description''}}

== Alternative usage ==
# Use {{para|align}} to override the default alignment
# Use {{para|size}} to override the default image size
# Use {{para|caption}} to override the default caption

